{"type":"message","id":"5fd03961","parentId":"8da45544","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:18:58.548Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oioapepxyqsf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 031816\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (Architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- Key insight: Compression and Causal Discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC experiment on the pulse log files. Let me check what files exist and what would be the most concrete next step.\r\n\r\nI should look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure, then implement a basic TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse log files exist and their format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to examine the existing pulse logs to understand their structure before implementing the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine the most recent pulse log to understand structure, then create a minimal TIC classifier prototype that can process pulse logs and identify invariant vs variant patterns. This advances the Phase 1 advancement toward the >70% classification goal.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - Experiment v0.1\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Target: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_metadata(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key-value pairs from pulse log header.\"\"\"\r\n    metadata = {}\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n        # Extract goals section\r\n        goals_match = re.search(r'### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n        if goals_match:\r\n            metadata['observation'] = goals_match.group(1).strip()\r\n        # Extract action section\r\n        action_match = re.search(r'### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n        if action_match:\r\n            metadata['action'] = action_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    return metadata\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n_recent=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load the N most recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = []\r\n    for f in LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"):\r\n        match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(f.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            pulse_files.append((match.group(1), f))\r\n    \r\n    pulse_files.sort(key=lambda x: x[0], reverse=True)\r\n    return pulse_files[:n_recent]\r\n\r\ndef identify_invariants(pulse_logs):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    TIC Core: Identify patterns that persist across ALL pulses = invariants.\r\n    Everything else = variant (session-specific).\r\n    \r\n    Invariant candidates:\r\n    - File paths that always appear in actions\r\n    - Goal/phase references that persist\r\n    - Structural patterns (### HEADING format)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    all_observations = []\r\n    all_actions = []\r\n    \r\n    for timestamp, filepath in pulse_logs:\r\n        meta = extract_pulse_metadata(filepath)\r\n        if meta.get('observation'):\r\n            all_observations.append(meta['observation'])\r\n        if meta.get('action'):\r\n            all_actions.append(meta['action'])\r\n    \r\n    # Word frequency analysis\r\n    all_text = ' '.join(all_observations + all_actions)\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z]{4,}\\b', all_text.lower())\r\n    word_counts = Counter(words)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants = words appearing in >80% of pulses\r\n    n_pulses = len(pulse_logs)\r\n    invariants = {w: c for w, c in word_counts.items() if c >= n_pulses * 0.8}\r\n    \r\n    # Variants = words appearing in <30% of pulses\r\n    variants = {w: c for w, c in word_counts.items() if c < n_pulses * 0.3}\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'invariant_words': invariants,\r\n        'variant_words': variants,\r\n        'total_pulses': n_pulses,\r\n        'vocabulary_size': len(word_counts)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, recent_pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Predict next pulse content based on invariant patterns.\r\n    Returns: confidence score for prediction accuracy.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    # Simplified: predict that invariants will appear in next pulse\r\n    # Real implementation would use actual sequence modeling\r\n    inv_count = len(invariants.get('invariant_words', {}))\r\n    return min(inv_count / 10.0, 1.0)  # Normalized confidence\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment on recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=== TIC Experiment v0.1 ===\")\r\n    print()\r\n    \r\n    pulse_logs = load_pulse_logs(n_recent=20)\r\n    print(f\"Loaded {len(pulse_logs)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_logs) < 5:\r\n        print(\"Insufficient data for TIC experiment\")\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    results = identify_invariants(pulse_logs)\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Vocabulary size: {results['vocabulary_size']}\")\r\n    print(f\"Invariant words (appearing in >80% pulses): {len(results['invariant_words'])}\")\r\n    print(f\"Variant words (appearing in <30% pulses): {len(results['variant_words'])}\")\r\n    print()\r\n    print(\"Top invariants:\")\r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:18:50\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336738547}}
